Preheat the #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Drain the @halloumi{225%g}, then slice lengthways into 1cm batons. Place into a small #bowl{} of cold water and leave to soak.

Spread the @McCain Home Chips{400%g} on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

When the oven is hot, bake on the middle shelf, ~{30-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large bowl, combine the @peri peri seasoning{1%sachet}, @olive oil{2%tbsp} and half the garlic. Season with salt and pepper.

Lay a @British chicken breast{1} onto your #chopping board{}, place your hand flat on top and slice into it from the side until there is 2cm left (be careful not to slice all the way through). Open it up like a book. Repeat with the other breast(s) - you've butterflied your chicken! IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Add the chicken to the bowl of peri peri marinade.

Mix well.

Lay the butterflied chicken on a lightly oiled large baking tray.

When the chips are halfway through cooking, turn them and pop back in the oven for the remaining time.

At the same time, add the chicken to the top shelf and bake until golden and cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice. Pop it into a large bowl along with the @coleslaw mix{120%g}, @mayonnaise{64%g} and half the @sweet chilli sauce{64%g}. Season with salt and pepper, then mix together. Set the slaw aside.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the @butter{10%g} and allow it to melt.

Once melted, add the @peas{120%g} and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Reduce the heat to medium, then add the @chilli flakes{pinch} and remaining garlic. Fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Transfer the peas to a bowl, season with salt and pepper, then cover to keep warm.

When the chips and chicken have 5 mins left, remove the chicken from the oven and drizzle over the @red pepper chilli jelly{37%g}. At the same time, sprinkle the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} over the chips and toss to coat. Return both to the oven for the remaining time.

Remove the halloumi slices from the cold water, pop them onto a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{} and pat them dry.

Wipe out the (now empty) frying pan and pop back on medium-high with a drizzle of oil (no need to clean).

Once hot, fry the halloumi until golden, turning frequently, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once the halloumi is golden, drizzle over the @honey{15%g} and turn to glaze it. Remove from the heat.

> If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

When ready, transfer the peri peri chicken to a #serving plate{} with the cheesy chips, honeyed halloumi, chilli peas and slaw in appropriately sized #serving bowls{} alongside.

Serve the remaining sweet chilli sauce on the side for dipping. Enjoy!